3
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:29,200
room and preflighting to get all the experiments ready to prepare the crew and the flight for

4
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:31,320
Apollo 16.

5
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:36,640
I think that looking back on it now we can say we had a very successful mission, that we

6
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:39,460
obtained a tremendous amount of information from the flight.

7
00:00:39,460 --> 00:00:44,580
I know that the rock boxes back there at the curatorial facility are bursting at their

8
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:48,460
seams and the geologists are going to have a lot to do.

9
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:54,380
I think also that because of the problems that arose and the necessity to change the

10
00:00:54,380 --> 00:00:58,600
